<div class="section">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="grid-12">
      <h2>Grid alignment</h2>
      <p>To align your grid elements to the start, center or end of a row just add the following modifier classes <code>row--align-left</code>, <code>row--align-center</code> or <code>row--align-right</code>.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row row--align-left demo">
    <div class="grid-4"><span>4</span></div>
  </div>
  <div class="row row--align-center demo">
    <div class="grid-4"><span>4</span></div>
  </div>
  <div class="row row--align-right demo">
    <div class="grid-4"><span>4</span></div>
  </div>

  <div class="row">
    <div class="grid-12">
      <pre><code>&lt;div class="row row--align-left"&gt;
  &lt;div class="grid-4"&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class="row row--align-center"&gt;
  &lt;div class="grid-4"&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class="row row--align-right"&gt;
  &lt;div class="grid-4"&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="section">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="grid-12">
      <h2>Grid ordering</h2>
      <p>At time you may need to move a column so there are tree new modifier classes for this first being <code>grid--order-last</code> which will move your grids to the last position, Next is the opposite <code>grid--order-first</code> which as you can imagine will move the grid to the first position, and last is the <code>row--order-reverse</code> which will reverse the order of all grids in your row.</p>
      <p>:last</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row demo">
    <div class="grid grid--order-last grid--order-first-mobile"><span>1</span></div>
    <div class="grid"><span>2</span></div>
    <div class="grid"><span>3</span></div>
    <div class="grid"><span>4</span></div>
    <div class="grid"><span>5</span></div>
    <div class="grid"><span>6</span></div>
  </div>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="grid-12">
